Implemented the controller policy and added visible UART-based self-tests.

What changed:
- `components/controller/controller.c`
  - Implemented fill/heat/hold/safe-idle behavior
  - Added stale-sensor detection using the 1000 ms timeout
  - Added low-fill heater guard
  - Added early heater-off on rising temperature near the upper band
  - Preserved safe heater state for hold behavior
- `components/controller/include/controller.h`
  - Added one internal controller field to track the safe heater state
- `agent_tests/test_controller_behavior.py`
  - Added firmware-level end-to-end UART probes covering boot, safe startup, fill, heat, low-level guard, early off, malformed input, stale timeout, and the temperature ceiling scenario

